The paper deals with the complexity of a graph coloring problem, which is a topic that falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem involves homomorphisms and constraints, which are common themes in computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses the concept of endo-triviality, which is a topic in group theory and algebraic structures, and may be relevant to logic and set theory (cs.LO). Finally, the paper deals with tournaments, which are a type of directed graph that are often studied in graph theory (cs.GT).
